folder: West End Avenue & 96th Street (West), Manhattan, NY
text:
740 West End Avenue at N.E. corner of 96th Street, "The Della Robbia", the original building erected on the site, some time between 1910 and 1916. The Riverside Theatre, shown on 96th Street, was built
about the same time.
The small house above it is the rather older "Theodora", five-story apartment house; it will be demolished about 1930. The building with the grocery store, shown in part on the N.W. corner opposite
The Della Robbia, was erected about 1900.
About 1920.
New York Sun Staff Photographer.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.

folder: West End Avenue & 96th Street (West), Manhattan, NY
text:
736 West End Avenue at S.E. corner of 96th Street, a new fireproof building nearing completion on the site of old 738 and 736. The two remaining old houses shown adjoining this building on West End Avenue are 734 and 732. Compare this with the pictures of these
houses about 1910.
About 1929.

folder: 96th Street (West) & West End Avenue, Manhattan, NY
text:
320 West 96th Street, south side, between West End Avenue and Riverside Drive. This vacant lot extends to Riverside Drive.
April 3, 1932.
P.L. Sperr.
